[ctns_make id='ptEqnS1']

    [ctns_front]
Particular Equation
    [/ctns_front]

    [ctns_back style='font-size:90%;max-width:400px']
An equation, e.g.,
$|y=3x+7|$
is called a <strong>particular equation</strong> when all constant values, e.g., $$m=3$$ and $$b=7$$, are specified.
    [/ctns_back]

    [ctns_backspeak]
An equation is called a particular equation when all constant values are specified.
    [/ctns_backspeak]

[/ctns_make]